    "aonid": 2376,
    "game-obj": "Equipment",
    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "Devotees of benevolent faiths fear and loathe corruption cassocks, each of which is dedicated to an unholy deity. When the garment chooses a target, such as when it senses a worshipper of a deity who isn\u2019t unholy, it alters its form to match another deity\u2019s iconography, appearing to be a devoted vestments for that deity. Once donned, the cassock tries to subtly sway its wearer to the worship of its deity. If the wearer begins to succumb, the *corruption cassock* gradually reverts to its true appearance, replacing its false iconography as its wearer converts.  \n  \nA *corruption cassock* functions as a *devoted vestments* for any wearer it chooses. Once you invest the cassock, it fuses to you. While you remain loyal to another deity, you believe the cassock grants you a +2 item bonus to Religion checks and a +1 item bonus to the divine skill of the deity to whom you believe the cassock is dedicated. It does neither. The GM secretly adjusts your checks with those skills, causing you to fail at religious tasks more often. If you have multiple equal or lower item bonuses to the affected skills, the cassock takes precedence, negating those bonuses. If you convert to following the cassock\u2019s true unholy deity, however, these bonuses function normally for you.  \n  \nIf you attempt to Cast a Spell that has the holy trait, the cassock can force you to attempt a DC 28 Will save. On a failure, you\u2019re stupefied 1 for one minute (stupefied 2 on a critical failure). A *corruption cassock* uses this ability to convince you that your deity has forsaken you.",
        "level": 11,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Rare",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 137,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 11,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "e4b0e4f5f4b3d4cad3bea67ec077e297",
                "text": "This rarity indicates that a rules element is very difficult to find in the game world. A rare feat, spell, item or the like is available to players only if the GM decides to include it in the game, typically through discovery during play. Creatures with this trait are rare. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creatures is increased by 5.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 26
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "rare"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Cursed",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 274,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "GM Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "GM Core pg. 306",
                            "alt": "GM Core pg. 306",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        },
                        "page": 306,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "93177649f9920e9a2a4a80ada85b7ab1",
                "text": "An item with this trait is cursed to cause trouble for its owner. A curse isn\u2019t detected when the item is identified, though a critical success reveals both the presence and exact nature of the curse. Cursed items can\u2019t be discarded once they\u2019ve been triggered or invested the first time. The item can be removed only if the curse is removed.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Divine",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 48,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 455",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 455",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 455,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "243cd4d729d5eddd1e2c4635b7985fb9",
                "text": "This magic comes from the divine tradition, drawing power from deities or similar sources. Anything with this trait is magical.  \n  \nA creature with this trait is primarily constituted of or has a strong connection to divine magic.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Focused",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 74,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "GM Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "GM Core pg. 221",
                            "alt": "GM Core pg. 221",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        },
                        "page": 221,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "53acdd8ebe1bdd9a5939d96ad87d005a",
                "text": "An item with this trait can give you an additional Focus Point. This focus point is separate from your focus pool and doesn\u2019t count toward the cap on your focus pool. You can gain this benefit only if you have a focus pool, and there might be restrictions on how the point can be used. You can\u2019t gain more than 1 Focus Point per day from focused items.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Intelligent",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 280,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "GM Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "GM Core pg. 304",
                            "alt": "GM Core pg. 304",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        },
                        "page": 304,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "79cfb7c5696e4ac278aba88f7237a815",
                "text": "An item with this trait is intelligent and has its own will and personality, as well as several statistics that most items don\u2019t have. Intelligent items can\u2019t be crafted by normal means, and they are always rare or unique.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "rare",
                        "alt": "rare",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 137
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "unique",
                        "alt": "unique",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 159
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Invested",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 98,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "GM Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "GM Core pg. 219",
                            "alt": "GM Core pg. 219",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        },
                        "page": 219,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "56b56ea5f9d865dc549f0ed7372ab504",
                "text": "A character can invest only 10 magical items that have the invested trait. None of the magical effects of the item apply if the character hasn\u2019t invested it, nor can it be activated, though the character still gains any normal benefits from wearing the physical item (like a hat keeping rain off their head).",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "invest",
                        "alt": "invest",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 2799
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Unholy",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 462",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 462",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 462,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "6309897c89780f17449b984cbb6d26cb",
                "text": "Effects with the unholy trait are tied to powerful magical forces of cruelty and sin. They often have stronger effects on holy creatures. Creatures with this trait are strongly devoted to unholy causes, and often have weakness to holy. If a creature with weakness to unholy uses an unholy item or effect, it takes damage from its weakness.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "holy",
                        "alt": "holy",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 517
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            }
        ],
